    <item>
      <title>Beacon and Module Layout —8-Beacon Setup</title>
      <link>https://factorioguides.com/production-ratios/beacon-module-guide/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 16:52:00 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>https://factorioguides.com/production-ratios/beacon-module-guide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Beacons amplify module effects across multiple buildings. &lt;div class=&#34;game-slot&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://factorioguides.com/images/icon/beacon.png&#34; alt=&#34;beacon&#34; class=&#34;game-img&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;game-name&#34;&gt;Beacon&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA; One beacon with &lt;div class=&#34;game-slot&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://factorioguides.com/images/icon/productivity_module_3.png&#34; alt=&#34;productivity_module_3&#34; class=&#34;game-img&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;game-name&#34;&gt;Productivity&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA; speed modules can boost 8 nearby assemblers —if you lay them out correctly.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;pro-tip&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TL;DR:&lt;/strong&gt; 8-beacon layout surrounds one assembler with 8 beacons. Fill beacons with speed modules, assemblers with productivity modules. Result: +30% productivity at +10% speed. The endgame standard for expensive recipes.&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;https://factorioguides.com/images/diagrams/8-beacon-layout.svg&#34; alt=&#34;8-beacon layout showing assembler surrounded by 8 beacons with module distribution&#34; class=&#34;schema-diagram&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; width=&#34;900&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-beacons-work&#34;&gt;How Beacons Work&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Beacons transmit module effects to nearby buildings:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Quality Modules — Space Age New Mechanic Explained</title>
      <link>https://factorioguides.com/space-age/quality-module-guide/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://factorioguides.com/space-age/quality-module-guide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;!-- Article Hero --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;article-hero-img&#34; style=&#34;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1a0a3a,#0a1a3a);height:200px;border-radius:8px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:Orbitron,sans-serif;font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;padding:0.3rem 0.6rem;border-radius:4px;background:#666;color:#fff;&#34;&gt;COMMON&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:Orbitron,sans-serif;font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;padding:0.3rem 0.6rem;border-radius:4px;background:#2ecc71;color:#fff;&#34;&gt;UNCOMMON&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:Orbitron,sans-serif;font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;padding:0.3rem 0.6rem;border-radius:4px;background:#3778c8;color:#fff;&#34;&gt;RARE&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:Orbitron,sans-serif;font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;padding:0.3rem 0.6rem;border-radius:4px;background:#9b59b6;color:#fff;&#34;&gt;EPIC&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:Orbitron,sans-serif;font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;padding:0.3rem 0.6rem;border-radius:4px;background:#e67e22;color:#fff;&#34;&gt;LEGENDARY&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-quality&#34;&gt;What Is Quality?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In Space Age, items can have &lt;strong&gt;5 quality tiers&lt;/strong&gt;. Higher quality items work better:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;table&gt;&#xA;  &lt;thead&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Tier&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Color&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;          &lt;th&gt;Bonus&lt;/th&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/thead&gt;&#xA;  &lt;tbody&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Common (1)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Gray&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Baseline&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Uncommon (2)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Green&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Plus 20 percent speed, minus 20 percent energy&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Rare (3)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Blue&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Plus 40 percent speed, minus 40 percent energy, plus 2 range&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Epic (4)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Purple&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Plus 60 percent speed, minus 60 percent energy, plus 4 range&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;      &lt;tr&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Legendary (5)&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Orange&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;          &lt;td&gt;Plus 80 percent speed, minus 80 percent energy, plus 6 range, plus 2 area of effect&lt;/td&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/tr&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/tbody&gt;&#xA;&lt;/table&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-quality-is-generated&#34;&gt;How Quality Is Generated&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality modules&lt;/strong&gt; in assemblers/machines give a chance for the output to be a higher quality tier.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
